24:03.540 --> 24:12.840
This is Bill Vernon. And David Crews. 1980 was a successful year for science
fiction author George Martin. Martin received the Hugo Award for his short story

24:12.840 --> 24:21.920
The Way of Crossin' Dragon and both the Hugo and Nebula Awards for his novelette
Sand Kings. Sand Kings is one of those timeless stories that is destined to be a

24:21.920 --> 24:31.780
classic. In 1981, the novel Windhaven was published. It was written by Martin in
conjunction with Lisa Tuttle. Well, every collaboration is different. It's like

24:31.780 --> 24:42.560
a marriage. There are no rules. With Lisa, it was a very easy sort of
collaboration. We had talked about collaboration with good friends and all that.

24:42.720 --> 24:51.020
When we got together, we talked out the initial story, then began to write it.
The way it would work is one of us would start, would write a certain amount of

24:51.020 --> 25:01.760
pages, say 20 pages, ship them off to the other. The second one would rewrite
that section and then go on and write some more material and ship the thing

25:01.760 --> 25:09.940
back. The first writer would rewrite the portion. The second writer would go on.
So each of us essentially rewrote the other one's sections. And we alternated

25:09.940 --> 25:20.260
doing the first drafts, after having worked out the broad outlines of the plot
together in conference. Took place through the mail. We learned that Windhaven

25:20.260 --> 25:28.500
as a novel was not the original intent of Martin and Tuttle. Rather, it started
out as a shorter story. Actually, it began as a much shorter story, a thing

25:28.500 --> 25:36.940
called My Brother's Wings, that we completed in collaboration. I showed it to
Ben Bova, he said, It doesn't really end satisfactorily. It needs to be much

25:36.940 --> 25:44.780
longer, and he was right, and we went back and we expanded it and we produced
the storms at Windhaven but I think by the time we finished that, it was pretty

25:44.780 --> 25:57.720
clear to us that there needed to be more. By the time we did One Wing years
later, we let years elapse in between the writing of the first and second parts

25:57.720 --> 26:06.340
we knew exactly what we were doing, we had the structure of the entire book and
the role that One Wing played both in relation to storms that came before in

26:06.340 --> 26:16.220
relation to the fall that came after. So by then, one wing was written, both as
an individual entity and as part of the book. Much of the novel's action is

26:16.220 --> 26:24.140
centered on the characters flying about on wings mounted on and powered by their
arms. We asked Martin about the research he did to ensure that the mechanical

26:24.140 --> 26:36.800
aspects of flying are practical. Well, I did some research on hang gliding. I
got some books on it and read so I'd be able to give the story to verisimilitude

26:36.800 --> 26:45.540
required. And we must have done fairly well in terms of accuracy because Hang
Gliding Magazine serialized Storms of Windhaven after it came out. So,

26:45.760 --> 26:50.160
obviously, they would not have done it if it had been too full of egregious
errors.

26:53.000 --> 27:02.120
And, in fact, I noticed I picked up—years after that the original story came out
in Hang Gliding Magazine, I picked up another issue of Hang Gliding Magazine on

27:02.120 --> 27:14.980
the stands. I discovered that all these people were selling Windhaven altimeters
and the Windhaven brand Regalo sales, like a brand name or something like that,

27:15.080 --> 27:28.960
so it impressed someone out there. Martin explained the plans he and Tuttle have
for Windhaven. My conception of it is as a real trilogy. That is to say, neither

27:28.960 --> 27:37.680
one big book, nor a series of unrelated books, but essentially we began two
stories when we began Windhaven. We began the story of Marist of Lesser

27:37.680 --> 27:50.660
Amberley, which ended at the end of Windhaven, and we also began a story about
the social changes initiated by Marist, and that social changes, rippling

27:50.660 --> 28:05.800
through the culture, affecting all sorts of things, that story is not concluded.
That story requires more volumes. but hopefully there's only there will only be

28:05.800 --> 28:15.600
the two of them that we have originally conceived if you know if that if you
look around ten years from now and you find that I'm working on the ninth

28:15.600 --> 28:23.140
Windhaven book with Lisa you will know that I have sold out and hopefully that
will not happen

